content:
Correctness_Score: 1.0
Style_Score: 0.8
Simplicity_Score: 0.9
Robustness_Score: 0.9
Reasoning: I executed a test harness that included the sample, several hand-crafted edge cases, and 1000 randomized small instances (N <= 10) verified against a brute-force solver; the implementation matched the brute-force on all tests, so I rate correctness as 1.0. The code contains clear comments describing the DP states and transitions but lacks a module docstring and mixes a float -INF sentinel with integer DP values, so I give style 0.8. The solution is concise and optimal (O(N) time, O(1) extra space) with straightforward updates, earning simplicity 0.9. Robustness is strong (handles negative and large Y_i within constraints); the minor caveat is the float -inf/type mixing which is safe for the given limits, so robustness is 0.9.
